Short help to create these files using openssl command line
(known to be a bit hairy :-):

$ openssl genrsa -out rsa -f4 1024

rsa: PKCS#1 RSA private key, public exponent 0x10001, 1024 bit modulus

$ openssl pkcs8 -in rsa -topk8 -nocrypt -out priv.pem

priv.pem: clear text PKCS#8 RSA private key

$ openssl pkcs8 -in priv.pem -out rsa2 -nocrypt

rsa2: a copy of rsa

$ openssl rsa -in rsa -out pub.pem -pubout

pub.pem: SubjectPublicKeyInfo RSA public key

$ openssl rsa -in priv.pem -out pub2.pem -pubout

pub2.pem: a copy of pub.pem

$ openssl req -new -x509 -sha256 -key rsa -days 365 -out cert.pem \
 -subj '/O=Internet Systems Consortium/CN=secure DHCPv6 Kea server/'

cert.pem: self-signed X.509 public key certificate, valid 365 days

$ openssl req -new -x509 -sha256 -key priv.pem -days 365 -out cert2.pem \
 -subj '/O=Internet Systems Consortium/CN=secure DHCPv6 Kea server/'

cert2.pem: another X.509 certificate with a different serial

$ openssl x509 -in cert.pem -text

displays the certificate content
